If $A$ is invertible, the equation $A\vect{x} = \vect{b}$ has the 
unique solution $\vect{x} = A\inv\vect{b}$. This is immediate:
\[
A\vect{x} = \vect{b} \implies A\inv(A\vect{x}) = A\inv\vect{b} 
\implies (A\inv A)\vect{x} = A\inv\vect{b} \implies \vect{x} = A\inv\vect{b}
\]
